This is a hospital. Do we discriminate based on identity?

27
00:04:49,840 --> 00:04:52,900
I'll do the second surgery after I finish the first one.

28
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:10,450
After suturing, send the patient to intensive care.

29
00:05:13,520 --> 00:05:14,160
Li,

30
00:05:14,440 --> 00:05:15,360
tell Dr. Chen

31
00:05:15,600 --> 00:05:17,120
I'll go in right away to perform his surgery.

32
00:05:17,120 --> 00:05:17,960
Dr. Chen asked me to tell you

33
00:05:17,960 --> 00:05:18,680
that patient Wan Quanyou

34
00:05:18,680 --> 00:05:20,560
shows no vital signs anymore.

35
00:05:35,080 --> 00:05:35,720
Later,

36
00:05:37,520 --> 00:05:39,040
the young man I saved

37
00:05:39,760 --> 00:05:41,090
was sent back to prison.

38
00:05:42,120 --> 00:05:43,320
Then he escaped again

39
00:05:43,880 --> 00:05:45,920
and killed a guard and another inmate.

40
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:47,380
He was sentenced to death.

41
00:05:49,120 --> 00:05:50,640
The victims' families

42
00:05:51,320 --> 00:05:52,800
saw me as his accomplice.

43
00:05:53,840 --> 00:05:57,200
Because I saved his life with my scalpel.

44
00:05:57,720 --> 00:05:59,159
Since then, my scalpel

45
00:05:59,159 --> 00:06:00,760
became a murder weapon.

46
00:06:00,760 --> 00:06:02,160
It's like a nightmare

47
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:03,680
that follows me everywhere.

48
00:06:03,680 --> 00:06:06,520
But Wan Xinxin, I want to tell you that until now,

49
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:07,800
I've never regretted it.

50
00:06:07,800 --> 00:06:09,560
I still believe I did nothing wrong.

51
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:11,000
I don't regret what happened that day.

52
00:06:11,000 --> 00:06:12,800
I made the right choice.

53
00:06:17,240 --> 00:06:18,360
Say that again.

54
00:06:18,360 --> 00:06:19,490
I did nothing wrong.

55
00:06:20,640 --> 00:06:23,280
Your choice was to save a bad person

56
00:06:23,280 --> 00:06:24,440
and abandon a good one.

57
00:06:24,440 --> 00:06:25,880
Allowing that criminal to continue hurting others.

58
00:06:25,880 --> 00:06:26,840
Is that right?

59
00:06:26,840 --> 00:06:27,880
Yes,

60
00:06:28,160 --> 00:06:29,120
I wanted to save him,

61
00:06:29,120 --> 00:06:30,880
but I was alone.

62
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,320
I wanted to save both of them.

63
00:06:32,320 --> 00:06:33,440
I told them to make arrangements.

64
00:06:33,440 --> 00:06:35,080
I said I'd come out and immediately save the other person.

65
00:06:35,080 --> 00:06:36,159
But I was alone.

66
00:06:36,159 --> 00:06:37,440
When I came out, being the only doctor there,

67
00:06:37,440 --> 00:06:38,680
your father was already gone.

68
00:06:38,680 --> 00:06:39,800
I didn't know it was your father.

69
00:06:39,800 --> 00:06:42,680
Stop talking. Just stop.

70
00:06:47,560 --> 00:06:49,960
Wan Xinxin, how can I make it up to you?

71
00:06:50,080 --> 00:06:51,159
What can I do to make amends?

72
00:06:51,159 --> 00:06:53,360
How can I heal your wounded heart?

73
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:55,520
I'll do anything to make it up to you.

74
00:06:55,720 --> 00:06:57,080
Just tell me.

75
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:00,280
You already have.

76
00:07:01,680 --> 00:07:04,080
While you were hiding this from me,

77
00:07:04,080 --> 00:07:06,360
you saved me and Bao.

78
00:07:07,440 --> 00:07:09,200
You fed us and gave us shelter,

79
00:07:09,640 --> 00:07:10,920
and helped me grow.

80
00:07:11,680 --> 00:07:13,520
You've already made amends.

81
00:07:15,360 --> 00:07:18,640
From now on, the two of us

82
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,480
owe each other nothing.

83
00:07:24,080 --> 00:07:24,880
Wan Xinxin.

84
00:07:26,400 --> 00:07:29,080
Believe me, when I found out about this,

85
00:07:31,600 --> 00:07:32,640
I was on my way

86
00:07:33,440 --> 00:07:34,480
I was on my way

87
00:07:35,159 --> 00:07:36,760
to the civil affairs bureau.

88
00:07:38,200 --> 00:07:39,800
I had just learned about it.

89
00:07:39,800 --> 00:07:42,000
I couldn't face you. I thought

90
00:07:42,920 --> 00:07:45,560
no matter what, I would only hurt you.

91
00:07:46,920 --> 00:07:48,240
I couldn't face you,

92
00:07:48,240 --> 00:07:49,800
so I chose to go to America.

93
00:07:49,800 --> 00:07:51,720
I thought going to America would help me forget you.

94
00:07:51,720 --> 00:07:52,640
But I want to tell you,

95
00:07:52,640 --> 00:07:54,840
every day and night in America,

96
00:07:54,840 --> 00:07:56,880
every moment I was thinking of you.

97
00:07:56,880 --> 00:07:59,480
I can't forget you because I love you.

98
00:08:01,240 --> 00:08:02,640
I love you, Wan Xinxin.

99
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,560
It's impossible for us now.

100
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:13,680
Wan Xinxin.

101
00:08:15,480 --> 00:08:17,840
Even if heaven played a joke on me,

102
00:08:19,200 --> 00:08:20,960
I think it was a beautiful joke.

103
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:21,720
From the moment you and Bao

104
00:08:21,720 --> 00:08:23,880
appeared in my car trunk,

105
00:08:24,440 --> 00:08:25,880
the beauty began.

106
00:08:31,000 --> 00:08:32,799
Can you give us some time?

107
00:08:36,840 --> 00:08:39,169
Please give me another chance to love you.

108
00:08:42,440 --> 00:08:43,440
It's impossible.

109
00:08:47,360 --> 00:08:48,320
Huaming.

110
00:08:49,760 --> 00:08:51,040
Forget about me.

111
00:08:52,520 --> 00:08:53,880
Forget about me.

112
00:08:54,880 --> 00:08:57,760
It's not that I don't want to love,

113
00:08:57,760 --> 00:09:00,560
even though I've been hurt before.

114
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:01,800
I can't forget.

115
00:09:02,880 --> 00:09:08,440
Who can predict the arrangements of fate?

116
00:09:08,880 --> 00:09:12,120
It's not that I don't want to love,

117
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:16,800
love has become vast as the ocean.

118
00:09:17,160 --> 00:09:23,000
Perhaps I'm destined to wait a lifetime.

119
00:09:25,200 --> 00:09:31,360
I thought after all the changes in life,

120
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:37,000
my heart would never race again.

121
00:09:39,200 --> 00:09:45,120
Yet I happened to meet you.

122
00:09:46,280 --> 00:09:50,960
But I no longer believe in love.

123
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:54,400
It's not that I don't want to love,

124
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:59,280
even though I've been hurt before.

125
00:09:59,480 --> 00:10:05,080
Who can predict the arrangements of fate?

126
00:10:05,280 --> 00:10:08,520
It's not that I don't want to love,

127
00:10:08,800 --> 00:10:13,360
love has sunk deep into the ocean.

128
00:10:13,680 --> 00:10:19,720
Perhaps I'm destined to wait a lifetime.

129
00:10:27,880 --> 00:10:29,480
Home is still the best place.

130
00:10:32,280 --> 00:10:34,680
If it weren't for Dr. Hua Ming this time,

131
00:10:35,160 --> 00:10:36,480
I really don't know

132
00:10:36,800 --> 00:10:38,600
if I could have made it back here.

133
00:10:41,800 --> 00:10:43,460
Mom, come sit down for a while.

134
00:10:48,120 --> 00:10:49,520
If you ask me,

135
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:52,120
heaven is looking out for you.

136
00:10:52,400 --> 00:10:54,080
You haven't even reached 100 years old yet,

137
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:56,540
so heaven doesn't have the heart to take you.

138
00:10:57,640 --> 00:10:59,040
You sure know how to talk.

139
00:10:59,080 --> 00:11:00,800
The doctor has already advised

140
00:11:00,800 --> 00:11:03,080
that you should avoid any emotional stress.

141
00:11:03,080 --> 00:11:03,960
You're right.

142
00:11:04,680 --> 00:11:06,680
I can't handle any stress right now.

143
00:11:07,400 --> 00:11:10,060
Especially smelling scents I shouldn't smell.

144
00:11:10,400 --> 00:11:12,440
Or seeing people I shouldn't see,

145
00:11:12,640 --> 00:11:14,120
that's what upsets me.

146
00:11:15,440 --> 00:11:17,240
Mom, what do you mean by that?

147
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:18,440
What do I mean?

148
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:21,250
As soon as I walked in, I smelled it.

149
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:24,200
Tell me, this perfume scent,

150
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:27,400
do you wear it or do I?

151
00:11:32,160 --> 00:11:33,080
Son.

152
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:35,960
While I'm in the hospital,

153
00:11:36,400 --> 00:11:38,480
you bring someone into our home.

154
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:42,090
Don't say I didn't warn you.

155
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:45,000
If you keep seeing Liu Wei,

156
00:11:46,720 --> 00:11:47,600
I will

157
00:11:48,400 --> 00:11:49,760
disown you as my son.

158
00:11:52,480 --> 00:11:53,240
Come in.

159
00:11:54,800 --> 00:11:55,400
Senior,

160
00:11:55,400 --> 00:11:56,200
Huaming.

161
00:11:56,680 --> 00:11:58,760
You came at the right time. Let's have dinner together tonight.

162
00:11:58,760 --> 00:11:59,880
Some friends from out of town are coming.

163
00:11:59,880 --> 00:12:01,410
I'll introduce them to you.

164
00:12:05,640 --> 00:12:07,800
Senior, I'll pass on dinner.

165
00:12:07,800 --> 00:12:09,860
I need to talk to you about something.

166
00:12:10,080 --> 00:12:11,120
Why so serious?

167
00:12:11,960 --> 00:12:12,880
Go ahead.

168
00:12:13,440 --> 00:12:15,200
There's a research institute in Shanghai.

169
00:12:15,200 --> 00:12:17,330
They want me to work on a project there.

170
00:12:18,240 --> 00:12:19,400
That's great!

171
00:12:20,080 --> 00:12:22,160
Why are you asking me about this?

172
00:12:22,480 --> 00:12:24,760
Working on a project in Shanghai is a good opportunity.

173
00:12:24,760 --> 00:12:26,490
It won't take that long either.

174
00:12:36,040 --> 00:12:36,840
You're not

175
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:39,480
planning to leave for good, are you?

176
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:42,250
That's exactly what I'm thinking.

177
00:12:42,440 --> 00:12:44,440
Once I leave, I won't be coming back.

178
00:12:47,000 --> 00:12:47,530
Huaming.

179
00:12:49,600 --> 00:12:51,480
You're the face of our hospital.

180
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:52,920
You can't leave.

181
00:12:53,560 --> 00:12:55,090
Face of the hospital or not,

182
00:12:55,680 --> 00:12:57,540
I haven't contributed much here.

183
00:12:57,840 --> 00:12:59,840
Of course, I must thank you, brother,

184
00:12:59,840 --> 00:13:02,200
for helping me return to practicing medicine.

185
00:13:02,200 --> 00:13:03,160
And also,

186
00:13:03,480 --> 00:13:05,360
Dr. Wei's investment

187
00:13:05,360 --> 00:13:08,000
in our hospital is still valid.

188
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:11,330
I'll make all the arrangements before I leave. Don't worry.

189
00:13:16,160 --> 00:13:19,240
So you're leaving after getting things done,

190
00:13:20,920 --> 00:13:22,920
retiring after achieving success?

191
00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:25,720
It's nothing like that.

192
00:13:28,280 --> 00:13:29,680
It's just that this city

193
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:33,970
has too many complications. I just...

194
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:38,530
don't want to stay anymore.

195
00:13:41,480 --> 00:13:44,280
You want to leave this place of heartbreak, right?

196
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:53,800
If you leave...

197
00:13:59,400 --> 00:14:00,040
Fine.

198
00:14:01,680 --> 00:14:04,920
You'll have more opportunities in Shanghai.

199
00:14:05,360 --> 00:14:07,090
Since you've made up your mind,

200
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:09,530
I won't try to keep you here.

201
00:14:15,280 --> 00:14:16,940
Just let me know before you go,

202
00:14:17,680 --> 00:14:18,880
and I'll see you off.

203
00:14:19,320 --> 00:14:19,850
Alright.

204
00:14:20,120 --> 00:14:22,200
I'll hand over my current work

205
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:23,890
and leave once that's done.

206
00:14:26,960 --> 00:14:28,160
Does Wan Xinxin know?

207
00:14:28,960 --> 00:14:29,680
No.

208
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:33,280
You should at least say goodbye to her.

209
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:36,520
Okay.

210
00:14:36,520 --> 00:14:38,380
Well, brother, I'll head out now.

211
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:55,400
You're finally here.

212
00:15:00,080 --> 00:15:01,010
Come in quickly.

213
00:15:04,680 --> 00:15:06,740
Have a seat. I'll get you some coffee.

214
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:12,720
I came to tell you.

215
00:15:14,400 --> 00:15:17,530
My mother just had surgery. She can't handle any stress.

216
00:15:20,520 --> 00:15:21,840
I can't upset her.

217
00:15:23,240 --> 00:15:24,240
If she finds out

218
00:15:24,240 --> 00:15:25,920
that we're still in contact,

219
00:15:26,760 --> 00:15:28,890
I'm afraid she won't be able to take it.

220
00:15:28,960 --> 00:15:29,800
So...

221
00:15:31,640 --> 00:15:32,480
So

222
00:15:33,520 --> 00:15:35,520
do you want to be with Wan Xinxin?

223
00:15:37,280 --> 00:15:37,920
No.

224
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:40,580
That's just my mother's own idea.

225
00:15:41,920 --> 00:15:44,850
There's no chance between me and Wan Xinxin anymore.

226
00:15:45,960 --> 00:15:48,480
What about us? Do we still have a chance?

227
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:50,920
You're not trying to break up with me, are you?

228
00:15:50,920 --> 00:15:52,400
That's not what I meant.

229
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:54,410
Please stop pressuring me.

230
00:15:54,880 --> 00:15:57,480
I can't take it anymore. I'm about to break down.

231
00:15:57,480 --> 00:15:59,480
Qin Gang, I'm not pressuring you.

232
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:00,840
I just want more time

233
00:16:00,840 --> 00:16:02,240
to be with you.

234
00:16:03,120 --> 00:16:05,320
Alright, let's not talk about this anymore.

235
00:16:05,320 --> 00:16:06,520
I need to get back quickly.

236
00:16:06,520 --> 00:16:07,560
I told my mother

237
00:16:07,560 --> 00:16:08,960
that I was meeting a client at the company.

238
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:10,020
I have to leave now.

239
00:16:10,120 --> 00:16:11,360
If I get back late,

240
00:16:12,200 --> 00:16:14,120
I'm afraid she'll get suspicious.

241
00:16:14,120 --> 00:16:15,240
Qin Gang, don't go.

242
00:16:15,440 --> 00:16:17,170
Please stay with me for a while.

243
00:16:17,560 --> 00:16:18,760
Just keep me company.

244
00:16:18,880 --> 00:16:20,280
I really can't right now.

245
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:22,200
Then I'll come see you at your office.

246
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:23,280
There are too many people at the office.

247
00:16:23,280 --> 00:16:25,280
My mother will definitely find out.

248
00:16:25,400 --> 00:16:26,480
From now on,

249
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:29,780
we can't contact each other anymore.

250
00:16:50,720 --> 00:16:51,440
Xinxin.

251
00:16:53,560 --> 00:16:55,960
I have to go. Let's meet up.

252
00:17:11,319 --> 00:17:12,280
What are you doing here?

253
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:13,410
You're not welcome.

254
00:17:14,560 --> 00:17:15,490
I came to see you.

255
00:17:15,760 --> 00:17:16,760
I don't need that.

256
00:17:18,200 --> 00:17:20,130
I'll just say a few words and leave.

257
00:17:20,880 --> 00:17:22,410
I have nothing to say to you.

258
00:17:23,839 --> 00:17:25,300
Let's talk about Qin Gang.

259
00:17:47,160 --> 00:17:47,960
Wan Renxian.

260
00:17:50,160 --> 00:17:51,840
Xu Huahua, where are you?

261
00:17:52,120 --> 00:17:54,000
What's wrong? You don't look happy.

262
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,160
There's something.

263
00:17:56,160 --> 00:17:57,360
I need your advice.

264
00:17:57,360 --> 00:17:58,800
Go ahead.

265
00:18:00,680 --> 00:18:02,210
Huaming says he's leaving.

266
00:18:03,400 --> 00:18:04,160
Leaving?

267
00:18:05,880 --> 00:18:06,800
Where is he going?

268
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:07,530
I don't know.

269
00:18:08,160 --> 00:18:10,720
